==English==
===Etymology===
{{OE.}} ''mædwe'', oblique case of ''mæd'' "meadow," from Proto-Germanic ''*mædwon'', from Proto-Indo-European ''*metwa-'' (''*me-'', "mow")
===Noun===
'''meadow'''
#A [[field]] or [[pasture]]; an area of low lying vegetation.
